[Nouns] circuit, roundabout way, digression, detour, circumbendibus, ambages, loop; winding (circuition) [more]; zigzag (deviation) [more].
[Verbs] perform a circuit; go round about, go out of one's way; make a detour; meander (deviate) [more].
lead a pretty dance; beat about the bush; make two bites of a cherry.
[Adjectives] circuitous, indirect, roundabout; zigzag (deviating) [more]; backhanded.
[Adverbs] by a side wind, by an indirect course; in a roundabout way; from pillar to post.
